> Creamy mash and green peas are a match made in heaven! Another amazing pairing? The
> creamy chive sauce and succulent beef rump that star in this delicious dish.

Boil a #large pot{} of @water{} with @salt{} for the @potatoes{3}.

Chop the potatoes into 2cm chunks (peeling optional).

Add the potatoes to the water and cook until fork tender, ~{12-18%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the #pot{}, off the heat.

Add a knob of @butter{} and a splash of @milk{to taste}(optional) or @water{to taste}
and mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with @salt{to taste} and
@pepper{to taste}. Cover to keep warm.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

== Creamy Chive Sauce ==

Place a #small pot{} over medium-high heat.

Add the @creme fraiche{110%grams} and half the @beef stock{1/2%sachet}.

Stir together and bring to the boil, then reduce the heat.

Simmer until slightly thickened, ~{3-5%minutes}.

While the sauce simmers, finely chop the @chives{5%grams} (use #scissors{} if you
prefer).

Stir three-quarters of the chives, @sweet chilli sauce{1%sachet} and
@?sugar{1/2%tsp} into the sauce.

Season to taste, then remove from the heat.

Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm.

== Beef ==

Place a #pan{} over high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Season the @irish beef rump{250%grams} with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fry the beef until browned, ~{1-2%minutes} each side for medium-rare.

Cook another ~{1-2%minutes} each side if you like it medium and a further
~{1-2%minutes} on each side if you want it well-done.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Meat is safe to eat
> when outside is browned.

Once cooked, transfer to a #board{}, cover and allow to rest.

== Peas ==

While the beef rests, wipe the now empty pan and return to medium-high heat with
a drizzle of @oil{}.

Fry the @peas{120%grams} until softened, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Reheat the creamy chive sauce if needed.

Slice the beef rump widthways into 2cm thick slices.

== To Serve ==

Share the beef rump between plates.

Serve the mashed potato and peas alongside.

Spoon the creamy chive sauce over the beef and mash.

Sprinkle the remaining chives over the dish.